FBIS4-40510 "drsov117_f_94011" FBIS-SOV-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 National Affairs Crimea's Meshkov Appoints Representatives in Moscow Crimea's Meshkov Appoints Representatives in Moscow LD1706095894 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2215 GMT 16 Jun 94 LD1706095894 Kiev UNIAR Ukrainian BFN [Text] Simferopol, 16 June -- Crimean President Yuriy Meshkov has issued an edict appointing Igor Vitrokhin as the Crimean trade and economic representative in Russia. Another edict, "On the Crimean Republic's permanent representation in the city of Moscow," appointed Viktor Silayev Crimea's as authorized representative in the capital of the Russian Federation.
